# The demo IG's package closure — single source of truth, consumed by
# fetch-packages.sh (download) and bundle-packages.sh (bundle). One <id>#<ver>
# per line; '#'-prefixed lines and blanks are comments.
#
# Why each package:
#   hl7.fhir.r4.core        — cycle is an R4 IG; the compile fishes R4 bases.
#   hl7.fhir.uv.tools.r4    — cycle sushi-config dependency.
#   hl7.terminology.r4      — cycle sushi-config dependency.
#   hl7.fhir.uv.extensions.r4 — cycle sushi-config dependency.
#   hl7.fhir.r5.core        — REQUIRED for snapshots even though cycle is R4:
#                             the walk engine is R5-internal, so R4 profile
#                             bases resolve against r5.core during snapshot
#                             generation (see sushi-rs demo/wasm-p2/prepare.sh).
#                             Removing it kills the snapshot-tree view.
hl7.fhir.r4.core#4.0.1
hl7.fhir.uv.tools.r4#1.1.2
hl7.terminology.r4#7.2.0
hl7.fhir.uv.extensions.r4#5.3.0
hl7.fhir.r5.core#5.0.0
